#week-title("Four", "The Personal Alchemical Almanac")

=== Core Teaching

The alchemical almanac is not a passive reference tool — it is an active
declaration of intent. By choosing in advance the auspicious moments for major
laboratory operations across an entire year, the practitioner aligns the Work
with the cyclical intelligence of the cosmos rather than operating at random
within it.

The natal chart, the personal year cycle (from NDT), and the electional
framework developed across this month now converge. The student designs their
own year-long operational calendar: when to begin a new maceration or
circulation, when to calcine, when to gather, when to seal.

*Major Planetary Configurations:* Beyond the daily and weekly cycles of
planetary hours, certain large-scale astronomical configurations carry unusual
weight for the alchemical practitioner:

- *Saturn–Jupiter conjunctions* (approximately every 20 years) mark generational
  thresholds in the Great Work. The traditional literature treats them as rare
  windows for undertaking a major commencement.
- *Saturn return* (approximately every 29.5 years) is understood in the
  Paracelsian tradition as a threshold of personal maturation — a time when
  whatever has been built must prove its genuine worth or be shed.
- *Solar and lunar eclipses* are regarded as intensifications of the corresponding
  planetary force. Eclipses are generally not used as elective moments for
  beginning operations, but for review and assessment.
- *Mercury retrograde* periods are traditionally avoided for beginning any Work
  that requires sustained accurate observation; they are suited instead to
  review, editing of records, and study.

*The Mundane Chakra.* The Hermetic Tree of Life Attributions table (HQ) lists
the "Mundane Chakra" of each sphere — the cosmic body that governs it. Saturn
governs Binah (the great limiting principle; the first fixed form); Jupiter
governs Chesed (expansion and multiplication); the Sun governs Tiphereth (the
heart of the Work; the gold principle). These attributions give the alchemical
almanac its deeper architecture: timing operations to the sphere that governs
them.

=== Topics This Week

- Designing the full-year alchemical almanac: tools and method
- Major planetary configurations and what each signals for the Work
- Saturn and Jupiter hours/days for lead and antimony work
- The Mundane Chakra: cosmic rulers of each sephiroth as timing agents
- Reviewing the natal chart within the electional framework
- Review of Month 5 progress and preparation for Quarter II Gathering

#inner-work[
  *Drawing the Personal Calendar*

  Using your natal chart, the current year's planetary ephemeris, and the
  personal year cycle (NDT Chapter 2), design a working alchemical calendar
  for the next twelve months.

  Mark the following at minimum:
  - New Moons and Full Moons (timing for extractions and calcinations)
  - Saturn and Jupiter stations and major aspects to natal positions
  - Planetary days and hours for at least two major laboratory beginnings
    you intend to undertake this year
  - Any Mercury retrograde periods (mark as review windows, not commencements)

  Record the calendar in your journal. Explain in one paragraph the logic
  behind your three most important elected moments.
]

